Comment:
Hello guys and girls, this is my first notation. 

Well, a classic move by white.
I have a different opening compared to the chess engines, soon you will see what I mean. Even though, my first move is alike.
Not what I expected, but it doesn't blows me off. Sending it unprotected?
I won't go and try to attack it. Stick to the opening, plus he can easilly protect it.
Having the knight at c3 is a great move since you have two pawns at line four.Plus nothing is attacking the pawns
Having the bishop there is a good play, since, it can attack what is attacking it and no knight is able to attact it due to the pawns around it.
Adding defence to the piece in the lead, helps you have control of your territory.

Moving the knight away for castling is a great way to let them know your king is not easy to capture. Moving it at f6 is a bad ideal, because it blocks the bisops attack. At h6 is also good, but I don't like to extend my territory attacks.
White is building a wall, which helps him control more of his territory. He now protected his c4 too.
Aha you thought I was going to castle, but the king is not close to  danger or under attact, so there is no need to castle so soon.
He is getting ready to castle so it won't get in the way later.
I have to have my second tower, but the real castles has four but when your facing one wall you see two towers.
He is trying to block my bishop's attack.
When you step in my four side of the lines you are now trasspassing and my dogs will attack.
Since I'm starting to attack. castling is a good move since all he has to do now is protect his pieces and attack.
MY TERRITORY!   >:O
With this move, his bishop will be able to move to more places.
I can't use a pawn to move him away except for f7, but castling just seems better.Since I'm being attack.
With this attack, he has force me to either block or attack.
I like to defend. I got three pieces already blocking it, and he is attaking with two.
